   <h2 class="Entry"><div class="title_link"><a href="http://www.thecoolhunter.co.uk/article/detail/1918/escape-machines-pop-up-in-paris--surprise">Escape Machines Pop Up in Paris - Surprise</a></div></h2>
   <span class="Small">March 25 2011<br /></span>
   <div class="Content">
   <p><iframe width="680" height="383" frameborder="0" src="http://player.vimeo.com/video/21479308?title=0&byline=0&portrait=0&color=dba9ab"></iframe></p>
<p>DDB Paris created this simple, fun &ldquo;Escape Machine&rdquo;&nbsp; experience for the French travel company Voyages <a href="http://www.voyages-sncf.com/" target="_blank">SNCF</a>.<br />
<br />
Menacing, glowing black cubes wait till someone goes close enough. Then  the cube asks where the person would like to travel. Pushing the red  button produces a crazy celebration, complete with gigantic walking  kisses, and provides the wishers large, customized mock tickets to their  destination. Watching the faces of the onlookers is just as much fun as  the experience itself!<br />
<br />
The underlying message is that the company&rsquo;s Escape service lets you  travel to any destination you want.&nbsp; DDB Paris with executive creative  director Alexandre Harve created this, as it did last year&rsquo;s flash-mob  &ldquo;Welcome Service&rdquo; scenes for Voyages SNCF. <em>- Tuija Seipell</em></p> 
   </div>
