   <span class="Entry">Events</span>
   <h2 class="Entry"><div class="title_link"><a href="http://www.thecoolhunter.co.uk/article/detail/1899/a-reallife-version-of-the-animated-film-up">A Real-Life Version of The Animated Film 'Up' </a></div></h2>
   <span class="Small">March 6 2011<br /></span>
   <div class="Content">
   <p><img src="http://www.thecoolhunter.net/images/up4.jpg" alt="" /></p>
<p>National Geographic Channel have created a real-life version of the animated  film Up &mdash; launching a house thousands of metres into the air using  balloons.</p>
<p>A team of scientists, engineers, and two   world-class balloon pilots successfully launched a 16' X 16' house 18'   tall with 8' coloured weather balloons from a private airfield east   of Los Angeles, and set a new world record for the largest balloon   cluster flight ever attempted.</p>
<p><img src="http://www.thecoolhunter.net/images/up1.jpg" alt="" /><br />
<br />
Using 300 helium-filled weather balloons, the lightweight building  reached an altitude of more than 3000m and remained in the air for about  an hour.</p>
<p><img alt="" src="http://www.thecoolhunter.net/images/upp.jpg" /></p>
<p><a target="_blank" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rV6rNqin4P8&amp;feature=player_embedded">The filming of the event, </a>from a  private airstrip, will be part of a new National Geographic Channel  series called How Hard Can it Be?, which will premiere in fall 2011.</p>
<p><img src="http://www.thecoolhunter.net/images/up2.jpg" alt="" /></p>
<p>See also <a href="http://www.thecoolhunter.net/article/detail/1476/cancer-council-australia--truth-or-dare-sydney" target="_blank">Cancer Council Australia, Truth or Dare event</a></p> 
   </div>
