   <span class="Entry">Events</span>
   <h2 class="Entry"><div class="title_link"><a href="http://www.thecoolhunter.co.uk/article/detail/1815/a-life-size-pinball-machine-you-can-play-in">A Life Size Pinball Machine You Can Play In</a></div></h2>
   <span class="Small">November 1 2010<br /></span>
   <div class="Content">
   <p><img width="680" height="484" alt="" src="../../../../images/pinball.jpg" /></p>
<p>THIS  is what we will want in our office now! Pinball may be living a second  life as a retro thing to do and own, but what we really want now is to  be living (or working, playing) IN a pinball machine!</p>
<p><img alt="" src="../../../../images/pinball1.jpg" /><br />
<br />
Our hopes for this were aroused by the super clever exhibit of <a target="_blank" href="http://www.supermodular.com/">Modular Lighting Instruments </a>at <a target="_blank" href="http://www.interieur.be/">Interieur 2010</a>, the 22nd International Design Biennale that took place October 15 &ndash; 24 at <a target="_blank" href="http://www.kortrijkxpo.com/">Kortrijk Xpo venue</a> in Kortrijk, Belgium .</p>
<p><img alt="" src="../../../../images/pinball2.jpg" /><br />
<br />
In a colourful and fun human-scale pinball machine, completely lit by LED  lights, Modular introduced its latest LED ceiling lights, Spock and  O&rsquo;Leaf, for the first time to the general public.</p>
<p><img alt="" src="../../../../images/pinball3.jpg" /><br />
<br />
The playing field of the game was divided into the same sections as the  Modular lighting catalogue: Orientation, Accent, General and Dynamic  making it easy for the &ldquo;players&rdquo;-- potential specifiers and buyers of  the new lights &ndash; to pay attention to the lights, and not just the fun  surroundings. Apparently, this energy-efficient exhibit used 70 % less  energy than the company&rsquo;s 2008 exhibit at the same event.</p>
<p><img alt="" src="../../../../images/pinball4.jpg" /><br />
<br />
The Roeselade, Belgium-based Modular Lighting Instruments has showrooms  across Europe and additional offices in the Netherlands and France.<br />
<br />
Both of the new fixtures, Spock and O&rsquo;Leaf, were designed by Bram Couvreur and Bjorn De Vos of <a target="_blank" href="http://www.couvreurdevos.be/">Couvreur &amp; Devos</a>, also located in Roeselade. <em>- Bill Tikos</em></p>
<p><img width="680" height="359" alt="" src="../../../../images/pinball5.jpg" /></p> 
   </div>
