   <h2 class="Entry"><div class="title_link"><a href="http://www.thecoolhunter.co.uk/article/detail/1462/portugese-pavilion--expo-zaragoza-08">Portugese Pavilion - Expo Zaragoza 08</a></div></h2>
   <span class="Small">January 16 2009<br /></span>
   <div class="Content">
   <br /><img src="http://www.thecoolhunter.net/images/stories/2007pics/storiesnew2007pics/marchpics/portugal4.jpg" /><br /><br />Held between June 14 and September 14, 2008, the International Exhibition Expo Zaragoza 2008 is already a distant memory but its effects still reverberate.<br /><br /><img src="http://www.thecoolhunter.net/images/stories/2007pics/storiesnew2007pics/marchpics/portugal3.jpg" /><br />&nbsp;<br />The 25 hectares along the river Ebro near Spain&rsquo;s fifth-largest city, Zarazoga, hosted thematic pavilions and thematic squares plus the pavilions of more than 100 countries, all exploring the overall theme of the Expo, &ldquo;Water and Sustainable Development.<br /><br /><img src="http://www.thecoolhunter.net/images/stories/2007pics/storiesnew2007pics/marchpics/portugal2.jpg" /><br />&nbsp;<br />Some of our favourite Expo mementoes are these spectacular images from the Portuguese Pavilion. Theming the Portuguese participation in the watery event, Lisbon-based <a href="http://www.bakgordon.com/" target="_blank" mce_href="http://www.bakgordon.com/">Bak Gordon Architects</a> envisioned a river&rsquo;s ever-changing flow from its trickling source to a river mouth by the sea.<br /><br /><img src="http://www.thecoolhunter.net/images/stories/2007pics/storiesnew2007pics/marchpics/portugal.jpg" /><br />&nbsp;<br />BAK created the pavilion&rsquo;s spaces as versatile, changeable and changing surroundings for audience participation at levels of each individual&rsquo;s choosing. The three main areas &ndash; Alert, Consciousness and Change &ndash; explored water and sustainability and featured a red &ldquo;river of pavement that helped the visitors track the flow of the exhibit.<br /><br /><img src="http://www.thecoolhunter.net/images/stories/2007pics/storiesnew2007pics/marchpics/portugal5.jpg" /><br />&nbsp;<br />From an alarming tubular &ldquo;jungle of Alert, to Consciousness where Nuno Cera&rsquo;s photography highlighted the three mighty rivers of Iberia &ndash; Guadiana, Tagus and Douro, the visitor ended up in the hopeful Change, where the promising movement of citizens was depicted, literally, with the movement of images and words spoken in various languages. <b>- Tuija Seipell</b><br /><br /><img src="http://www.thecoolhunter.net/images/stories/2007pics/storiesnew2007pics/marchpics/portugal7.jpg" /><br /><br />Photography by <a href="http://www.ultimasreportagens.com/" target="_blank" mce_href="http://www.ultimasreportagens.com/">ultimasreportagens.com</a><br /><br /><br /> 
   </div>
