   <h2 class="Entry"><div class="title_link"><a href="http://www.thecoolhunter.co.uk/article/detail/1369/creative-brands-rising-above-the-noise-at-beijing-olympics">Creative Brands Rising Above The Noise At Beijing Olympics </a></div></h2>
   <span class="Small">August 15 2008<br /></span>
   <div class="Content">
   <p><br />
<img src="http://www.thecoolhunter.net/images/stories/2007pics/storiesnew2007pics/marchpics/minibeijing.jpg" alt="" /><br />
<br />
Forget the sport..some of the most interesting things happening at the Beijing Olympics are coming from clever sponsors who have dreamt up creative ways to promote their brands at the mega global event. We're loving the offering from Mini Cooper, who have dragged traditional Chinese street transport into the 21st century with these great bike-powered Minis. Samsung has been equally creative, giving Olympics' fans a chance to view all of the action from their own &quot;private&quot; alien-like pods. Both of these offerings are a lesson to global brands: get creative and innovative in your marketing or risk being drowned out by the noise. <i><b>- Laura Demasi</b></i><br />
<br />
<img src="http://www.thecoolhunter.net/images/stories/2007pics/storiesnew2007pics/marchpics/samsungolympics.jpg" alt="" /></p> 
   </div>
   <div class="EntryTools">
   	  <div class="EntryToolsLeft">
			Share It: 
